# This blueprint is not meant to be an optimal production blueprint, but rather be a MVP/POC blueprint to showcase some of the capabilities in VCF Automation. To make it work there are some things that can not currently (9.0.2) be fetched dynamically that you need to input.
# most of these values are under variables: , but you also need to edit the "vmi-" for your ubuntu image in the content catalogue.
# you also need to create a secret under "Administer" -> "Secrets" called ad-join-password
# this blueprint will create a Ubuntu deployment using the supplied ubuntu-cloudimg ovfs, join it to active directory, and setup syslog to VCF Operations for logs.

# in VCF Automation AllApps version 9.0.2, there is no way to use bcrypt() in blueprints, the hashed password for vmware user is VMware123!

formatVersion: 2
